# Numara — environment template.
# Copy to `.env.local` and fill in real values. NEVER commit `.env.local`.
# Values are NOT carried by git, so you must populate these on every new machine.

# --- Supabase (recoverable any time from the Supabase dashboard) ---
# Project Settings → API. Must point at the SAME project on every machine.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# --- Secret encryption key (NOT stored anywhere but this file) ---
# 32-byte AES-256 key (64 hex chars) used to encrypt/decrypt rows in
# public.system_secrets — including the OpenRouter API key. Separate from
# the Supabase keys per PRD §8.
#
# This value lives ONLY in .env.local. It is not in Supabase and not in git.
# Carry the existing value across to any new machine (password manager /
# encrypted transfer). If you generate a fresh one instead, the stored
# OpenRouter key becomes undecryptable and must be re-entered in
# /admin/secrets under the new key. Generate with:
#   openssl rand -hex 32
SECRET_ENCRYPTION_KEY=
